narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I'm amazed how much Portuguese we were able to learn over the course of this semester with Fabi. She's so passionate about teaching and the language, which made us all excited to learn each day.

Over the course of PORT 140, I learned to refine the skills learned in PORT 130 such as verb use, vocabulary, and grammar, but I also learned to be more confident expressing my thoughts through writing and speaking.
I learned more about the Portuguese language and even learned how to read and understand Portuguese literature. I saw my own growth, which felt nice.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Fabi is simply one of the best instructors I've had at Yale, if not the best: she cares so much about her students and is dedicated to their success completely. All of the material was interesting and helped to develop our fluency in the language.
The structure is a little less organized but I LOVED THIS CLASS!!!!!!

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: This was one of my favorite classes at Yale. I'd highly recommend it for a relaxed environment that teaches you a lot.
